# Hermes fleet (Cursor)

Read the canonical guide: `website/docs/user-guide/features/cursor-hermes.md`.

## Session start (declarative bootstrap)

Prefer one consolidated MCP read when available; otherwise call in order:

1. `fleet_context_snapshot()` — if present on the Hermes MCP server
2. Else: `agents_list(include_heartbeat=true)` → `learnings_read()` → `knowledge_read(artifact="latest_state")` → `knowledge_read(artifact="held_spec_ledger")`

Before changing a named agent: `skills_read(name="<agent>")` and `agents_get(name="<agent>")`.

## Two MCP modes (do not conflate)

| Mode | Requires gateway | Use for |
|------|------------------|---------|
| **Skills / context** | No | SOUL.md, registry, learnings, knowledge layer, artifacts |
| **Live ops / messaging** | Yes | conversations, send_message, approvals, events |

## Source of truth (precedence)

Higher rows win over lower when they conflict:

| Layer | Role |
|-------|------|
| Runtime wrappers / cron / production scripts | Execution truth |
| `HERMES_AGENTS_DIR` … `SOUL.md` / `IDENTITY.md` / `HEARTBEAT.md` | Behavioral truth |
| `AGENT_REGISTRY.json` | Index and discovery only |
| Knowledge layer artifacts | Operational state |
| `.learnings/` | Memory and operator notes |
| `CLAUDE.md` / this rule | Workflow constraints for the IDE session |

Registry metadata must never override runtime identity documents.

## Paths

Set machine-specific values in `.cursor/mcp.json` (copy from `.cursor/mcp.json.example`). Do not commit host-specific paths to the shared repo.

Verify setup: `hermes doctor` (MCP checks planned).
